node.text: We had finished playing soccer at the Zimbabwe orphanage and the adults were chatting when someone said, “Look over at Manilla!” He and a girl had started playing catch and we’re just in their own little world together.. 😍🥰😭 Seeing this made our hearts sing!! The teachers at the orphanage were making a pretty big deal about it and it wasn’t until later that they explained to us that she hadn’t been talking or interacting with anyone, so to see her doing this was very special! ❤️💙💚 Thank you, Ethandweni Children's Home for the invitation to visit, play and interact with the kids, and take some videos and share your stories! We do our best to make a positive impact, BUT as as always, we seem to be the ones so deeply impacted. THANK YOU! Next week @thebucketliststudios is launching new Adventure Bands and 50% of the profits will go directly to this orphanage. We hope you will join us in supporting! 🌍

node.text: At the end of the day we will offload our cameras to organize and watch our footage. It’s always such a fun joy seeing what special moments we missed that the cameras captured. WE HAD NO IDEA this even happened to @manillagee. He literally picked himself up and jumped back on the horse (after emptying the sand from his trunks and meeting a friendly pup;) 😅🐶😍

node.text: FAMILY MOVIE NIGHT watching #YouvsWild on @netflixfamily! 🦁🐒🦁 We embarked on an at-home mission to watch the new interactive movie "Animals on the Loose"! With family-friendly choices around every corner, we guided @beargrylls through his adventures as he wrangled the animals back to safety while we called the shots from the comfort of our living room. Stream and play along now, only on @Netflix, and show us how you're watching with your family using #YouvsWild 🗺️

node.text: An important part of being a parent is sometimes putting on a brave face for your kids even though inside you might be all sorts of terrified and stressed! 😰 Did you see our Instagram stories?? Our little plane had to abort on takeoff because an engine failure! Our pilot safely guided us off the runway and we waited for the mechanics to arrive. I was STRESSING so Garrett took the kids to the side..and well..they danced in the sunset..😌

node.text: We had finished playing soccer at the Zimbabwe orphanage and the adults were chatting when someone said, “Look over at Manilla!” He and a girl had started playing catch and we’re just in their own little world together.. 😍🥰😭 Seeing this made our hearts sing!! The teachers at the orphanage were making a pretty big deal about it and it wasn’t until later that they explained to us that she hadn’t been talking or interacting with anyone, so to see her doing this was very special! ❤️💙💚 Thank you, Ethandweni Children's Home for the invitation to visit, play and interact with the kids, and take some videos and share your stories! We do our best to make a positive impact, BUT as as always, we seem to be the ones so deeply impacted. THANK YOU! Next week @thebucketliststudios is launching new Adventure Bands and 50% of the profits will go directly to this orphanage. We hope you will join us in supporting! 🌍

node.text: First Garrett went with Manilla. Then Dorothy and I went together. Afterwards, Dorothy asked to go again but neither Garrett or I wanted to go again. So she asked her little brother, 7 yr old Manilla, AND HE SAID YES!! 😨🥰🥲 @thebucketlistfamily @dorothygee @manillagee

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by The Bucket List Family on August 14, 2021 tagging @thebucketlistfamily. May be an image of 1 person, child, standing and outdoors.

node.text: 6 YEARS!! 🤯 Tomorrow August 15th will mark 6 years since the day we sold everything and left our home (actually it was a small apartment) in Utah to travel the world. We traveled to 50 countries together and then returned back to Utah for the birth of baby Cali. Since his birth we have visited another 36 countries, 86 countries total, and found a very special place to call home amongst the island of Hawaii. Life is crazy how 1 decision can change so much of the future.. THANK YOU EVERYONE for being a part of our journey, a part of our new small business, and most importantly, A PART OF OUR BUCKET LIST FAMILY AROUND THE WORLD! 🌍💚💙❤️🌏

node.text: This moment brought me to tears.. 🥲😍🥲 Cali saw this little boy playing with some rocks and started to give him some rocks he found, almost like a peace offering to friends.. ❤️💙💚 If you swipe through these photos you can see this very special moment when the boy was curious of Cali’s unique hair. Cali brings up his hands like, “what kind of greeting are we doing here?” And then they put their hands together and just stared at the differences AND THE SIMILARITIES..💚🌍💚 @caligee @thebucketlistfamily

node.text:
You know the phrase “Monkey see monkey do”..? How about, “Elephants see Dorothy do”..!? 🐘🥰🐘
Want to come to this amazing place with your family or friends? Are you a Bucket List Friend? That’s the name of our monthly email subscription that includes our monthly podcast video and an exclusive travel deal. This next month’s is a crazy amazing deal to this place! Check it out and sign up on our website thebucketlistfamily.com/friends ❤️💙💚
